A basic outline for how to install PEBIL.

1. System Requirements
Operating System        Linux
Binary Format           Elf
Architecture            X86 or X86_64
Other                   To call instrumentation functions from a shared library
                        the system must have dynamic linking enabled. Also requires
                        the gnu linker to be used.


2. Add the following to your shell login script (assuming the installation is
at /path/to/pebil/)

bash:
PEBIL_ROOT=/path/to/pebil/
PEBIL_LIB=${PEBIL_ROOT}/lib
PEBIL_BIN=${PEBIL_ROOT}/bin
PEBIL_LD_FLAGS="-Wl,--hash-style=sysv -Wl,-T,${PEBIL_ROOT}/linker/pebil_ld_script"
PEBIL_LD=ld
PEBIL_GFORT=gfortran
PATH=${PATH}:${PEBIL_BIN}
export PEBIL_ROOT
export PEBIL_LIB
export PEBIL_BIN
export PEBIL_LD_FLAGS
export PEBIL_LD
export PEBIL_GFORT
export PATH

csh:
setenv PEBIL_ROOT /path/to/pebil/
setenv PEBIL_LIB ${PEBIL_ROOT}/lib
setenv PEBIL_BIN ${PEBIL_ROOT}/bin
setenv PEBIL_LD_FLAGS "-Wl,--hash-style=sysv -Wl,-T,${PEBIL_ROOT}/linker/pebil_ld_script"
setenv PEBIL_LD ld
setenv PEBIL_GFORT gfortran
setenv PATH ${PATH}:${PEBIL_BIN}

3. build 
`gmake` from the top-level directory

4. run
Details on how to run:
pebil --help

Examples:
pebil --typ jbb --app testapps/dynTest.gnu
pebil --lib lib --typ ide src/pebil